.TH smi-decrypt "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Base Command"
.SH NAME
smi-decrypt \- Decrypt a file encrypted with smi-encrypt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-decrypt
.I ENCRYPTED_FILE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-decrypt
decrypts the specified \fIENCRYPTED_FILE\fR (usually with a \fB.enc\fR suffix) using OpenSSL with the AES-256-CBC algorithm.
Upon successful decryption (result code 0 and non-empty output), the encrypted file is removed and the original file is restored.
.PP
Decryption uses 10,000 iterations for key derivation, matching the encryption process.
.SH AUTHOR
